I'm so sorry.

244
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:48,548
There's an emergency.

245
00:12:48,951 --> 00:12:53,445
Nora, I have to go to the hospital,
but I can be back in less than an hour.

246
00:12:53,589 --> 00:12:54,920
It's okay, I'll go.

247
00:12:55,057 --> 00:12:57,025
No, no, no.

248
00:12:58,961 --> 00:13:00,019
This could be good.

249
00:13:00,162 --> 00:13:01,220
It's an exercise.

250
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:04,389
Because you're out in the world,
but you're in here safe, secure.

251
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:07,559
You can practice your breathing,
your visualizations.

252
00:13:08,437 --> 00:13:12,635
- I can't.
- Mom, please, you need to do this.

253
00:13:16,345 --> 00:13:17,835
PETE: It's not that simple, Sam.
SAM: It is.

254
00:13:17,980 --> 00:13:20,813
Doesn't matter how long we've known him
or how much we wanna spare him,

255
00:13:20,950 --> 00:13:23,475
we cannot have a hand
in ending a man's life.

256
00:13:23,619 --> 00:13:26,247
- He's asking for a prescription.
- Which he knows how to use

257
00:13:26,388 --> 00:13:27,753
to kill himself.

258
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:30,859
Now we know he knows
and we know what he's gonna do,

259
00:13:30,993 --> 00:13:32,358
so let's just stop pretending.

260
00:13:32,495 --> 00:13:34,360
There are laws
against assisted suicide.

261
00:13:34,497 --> 00:13:37,330
There's no one coming after us, Sam.
There's no family to consider.

262
00:13:37,466 --> 00:13:39,730
There's just Alexander,
and he wants to die.

263
00:13:40,703 --> 00:13:42,898
- Who wants to die?
- Patient with pancreatic cancer.

264
00:13:43,038 --> 00:13:46,201
Stage 4-B pancreatic cancer,
and he's a doctor.

265
00:13:46,342 --> 00:13:48,139
Well, if he's a doctor,
he's gonna find a way.

266
00:13:48,277 --> 00:13:50,404
- He wants morphine.
- Which we should give him.

267
00:13:50,546 --> 00:13:52,776
That's kind of going out
on a limb there, Dr. Kevorkian.

268
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:54,974
He's gonna do this.
Will you really sleep better

269
00:13:55,117 --> 00:13:57,915
knowing that we stood passively by
rather than actively help him?

270
00:13:58,053 --> 00:14:02,251
I will sleep better if I know that I took
seriously the oath to first do no harm.

271
00:14:02,391 --> 00:14:05,019
Well, what does more harm,
helping him die or letting him live?

272
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:07,856
Exactly. Alexander has nothing left

273
00:14:07,997 --> 00:14:11,228
but the chance to control
when and how the end comes.

274
00:14:11,367 --> 00:14:12,401
This is... It's mercy, this is not murder.

275
00:14:12,401 --> 00:14:14,392
This is... It's mercy, this is not murder.

276
00:14:14,537 --> 00:14:16,596
It's a fine line, boys. A slippery slope.

277
00:14:16,739 --> 00:14:19,435
SAM:
Look, I understand the concept of mercy,

278
00:14:19,575 --> 00:14:22,635
but letting nature run its course
is different than helping nature along.

279
00:14:23,045 --> 00:14:24,910
It doesn't matter
how we try to rationalize it.

280
00:14:25,047 --> 00:14:28,539
There is no moral difference
between writing him a prescription

281
00:14:28,684 --> 00:14:29,742
and buying him a gun.

282
00:14:29,885 --> 00:14:32,718
I won't do it. The practice won't allow it.

283
00:14:33,889 --> 00:14:37,791
The Sinclairs, they're probably
not gonna go through with the adoption.

284
00:14:37,927 --> 00:14:39,519
What?

285
00:14:39,662 --> 00:14:40,720
Because he's sick?

286
00:14:40,863 --> 00:14:42,421
Let's not worry about them right now.

287
00:14:42,565 --> 00:14:45,557
- What's gonna happen to him?
- We'll find other good parents.

288
00:14:46,001 --> 00:14:48,162
VIOLET:
But right now, he needs surgery.

289
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:49,601
And without your consent,

290
00:14:49,738 --> 00:14:52,832
the hospital won't allow Dr. Montgomery
to do what she thinks is best for him.

291
00:14:53,108 --> 00:14:55,269
She told me before, I had to choose.

292
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:59,581
I don't think I can choose...
I don't think I can choose and then let go.

293
00:14:59,715 --> 00:15:02,684
I think you've been choosing
what's best for the baby all along.

294
00:15:03,552 --> 00:15:05,520
You've been planning
the best life possible

295
00:15:05,654 --> 00:15:08,452
and all Dell is asking is
that you plan one more thing.

296
00:15:08,757 --> 00:15:11,692
You just need to sign a form.
Okay, one form.

297
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:14,387
And you'll have an incredible team
of doctors looking after him.

298
00:15:15,564 --> 00:15:18,089
He needs you. One last time.

299
00:15:24,807 --> 00:15:26,604
Paper's signed. You're good to go.

300
00:15:26,742 --> 00:15:28,539
- Judy came through.
- Yeah, for now.

301
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:31,271
I'm still hoping
that the Sinclairs will come through.

302
00:15:31,413 --> 00:15:33,142
They walked in a crisis.

303
00:15:33,282 --> 00:15:36,774
- Would you want that for your kid?
- We should talk about something else.

304
00:15:36,919 --> 00:15:39,752
Like who you're dating, the colleague
you refuse to tell me about?

305
00:15:39,888 --> 00:15:41,947
Well, you're one to talk.
What about Wyatt?

306
00:15:42,091 --> 00:15:46,460
Why is everyone so stuck on what did
or didn't happen with Wyatt?

307
00:15:46,595 --> 00:15:48,688
Well, who else is stuck on it?
You didn't tell Kevin?

308
00:15:48,831 --> 00:15:50,628
No, there's nothing to tell.
It didn't happen.

309
00:15:50,766 --> 00:15:53,257
I didn't cheat, I didn't go out on the date.

310
00:15:53,402 --> 00:15:55,962
- I just went into his office and kissed him.
- Pardon me?

311
00:15:56,105 --> 00:15:58,471
And then I walked out.
So technically, it wasn't cheating.

312
00:15:58,607 --> 00:16:01,167
Technically, you walked into his office
and you kissed him...

313
00:16:01,310 --> 00:16:04,905
And stopped, and I left,
and I have not seen him since.

314
00:16:05,047 --> 00:16:08,244
Kevin keeps asking where I was,
and I keep telling him I was working,

315
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:11,217
and I divert him with sex,
but it was nothing.

316
00:16:11,353 --> 00:16:14,220
Well, if it was nothing,
then why did you wait a week to tell me?

317
00:16:14,556 --> 00:16:16,581
[EKG BEEPING]

318
00:16:18,761 --> 00:16:20,786
Baby's sats are falling.
Getting hard to ventilate.

319
00:16:20,929 --> 00:16:23,659
Take him off the vent and bag him.
I gotta go in now.

320
00:16:27,136 --> 00:16:28,501
[SIGHS]

321
00:16:28,637 --> 00:16:31,902
Nora, I'm so sorry, I was just...

322
00:16:34,677 --> 00:16:36,167
Nora?

323
00:16:38,614 --> 00:16:40,241
Have you seen your mother?

324
00:16:40,382 --> 00:16:41,849
She's not in your office?

325
00:16:41,984 --> 00:16:43,212
Maybe she's in the bathroom.

326
00:17:20,689 --> 00:17:24,625
Nora, are you in there?

327
00:17:25,561 --> 00:17:27,324
NORA:
Yes.

328
00:17:28,931 --> 00:17:30,899
Do you wanna come out?

329
00:17:32,067 --> 00:17:33,625
No.

330
00:17:40,042 --> 00:17:41,566
Sorry.

331
00:17:48,517 --> 00:17:49,575
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

332
00:17:49,718 --> 00:17:51,652
It's open.

333
00:17:54,923 --> 00:17:57,756
Peter, lovely to see you.

334
00:17:58,160 --> 00:18:01,652
I'm treating myself
to chocolate pudding.

335
00:18:01,797 --> 00:18:02,855
My favorite.

336
00:18:02,998 --> 00:18:05,057
You brought my medicine?

337
00:18:08,103 --> 00:18:11,334
I wanted to tell you in person.
I'm sorry.

338
00:18:11,473 --> 00:18:15,307
We just can't prescribe drugs
to help you kill yourself.

339
00:18:16,478 --> 00:18:19,504
I understand.
Yeah, I wasn't counting on it.

340
00:18:19,848 --> 00:18:21,713
In my day, it might have been different.

341
00:18:21,850 --> 00:18:25,013
A doctor's job was to preside
over life and death.

342
00:18:25,154 --> 00:18:28,555
I know what you want,
but you are still alive.

343
00:18:28,690 --> 00:18:30,681
You're still handling the pain,
and you have time.

344
00:18:30,826 --> 00:18:34,353
Not much, but time.

345
00:18:34,496 --> 00:18:36,191
And what would I do with this time?

346
00:18:36,331 --> 00:18:40,461
- I'm 73 years old.
- You could

347
00:18:40,602 --> 00:18:43,901
get closures, say your goodbyes,
enjoy your last days.

348
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:46,098
Peter, I'm the last of my friends
left alive.

349
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:49,511
I have no lover, no children, no one.

350
00:18:49,645 --> 00:18:52,808
In the coming days,
I'm gonna gradually...

351
00:18:54,483 --> 00:18:55,814
...fade away.

352
00:18:55,951 --> 00:18:57,578
I'll either be in extraordinary pain

353
00:18:57,719 --> 00:19:01,678
or I'll be so high on drugs
that I might as well be dead.

354
00:19:01,824 --> 00:19:06,193
I don't believe those are last days
I'd like to enjoy.

355
00:19:08,363 --> 00:19:10,854
Well, you're enjoying sugar.

356
00:19:10,999 --> 00:19:13,092
Oh, this isn't sugar.

357
00:19:14,102 --> 00:19:15,160
It's a mixture.

358
00:19:15,304 --> 00:19:19,798
Sixteen alprazolam tablets
from my bathroom,

359
00:19:19,942 --> 00:19:23,776
12 dusty codeine tablets
from the hall bathroom,

360
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:26,506
a couple of muscle relaxants,
some sleeping pills,

361
00:19:26,648 --> 00:19:32,416
and a tiny bit of LSD leftover
from a fabulous party in 1972.

362
00:19:32,554 --> 00:19:35,489
- Alexander.
- No, don't bother.

363
00:19:35,891 --> 00:19:37,449
It's okay.

364
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:40,027
I'm already on my second bowl.

365
00:19:40,395 --> 00:19:42,260
I told you.

366
00:19:42,731 --> 00:19:44,528
I'm gonna die.

367
00:19:58,113 --> 00:20:01,480
COOPER: Hey. Look, I really need
your advice. I am in a situation...

368
00:20:01,617 --> 00:20:04,177
- Cooper, not a good time here.
- Okay, not how I imagined it.

369
00:20:04,319 --> 00:20:07,755
Not that I ever imagined being
proposed to. That's kind of crazy, right?

370
00:20:07,890 --> 00:20:12,156
I don't know if I can trust her,
but I love her, I think.

371
00:20:12,294 --> 00:20:15,991
I do. No, I do.
And I am happier now than I was before.

372
00:20:16,131 --> 00:20:19,123
I mean, I was miserable before.
I don't know if I'm really ready to...

373
00:20:19,268 --> 00:20:21,793
Cooper, I am with a patient.

374
00:20:22,871 --> 00:20:24,532
Oh, the agoraphobic?

375
00:20:27,175 --> 00:20:30,406
Sorry. You should come out,
weddings are great.

376
00:20:33,916 --> 00:20:37,352
VIOLET: Sorry about that interruption.
NORA: That's okay, I don't mind.

377
00:20:37,486 --> 00:20:40,683
I'm guessing it's uncomfortable in there.

378
00:20:40,822 --> 00:20:46,124
Let's... Let's try and get a fresh start
on the couch.

379
00:20:46,261 --> 00:20:49,594
I'm not coming out,
and I'm not going to that wedding.

380
00:20:49,731 --> 00:20:51,631
I can't.

381
00:20:53,201 --> 00:20:54,634
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

382
00:20:55,938 --> 00:20:57,098
Baby's out of surgery.

383
00:20:57,239 --> 00:20:58,399
Okay, it went well.

384
00:20:58,540 --> 00:21:02,738
Addison was amazing,
so I thought you'd like to know.

385
00:21:02,878 --> 00:21:05,870
Dell, I can't stop thinking about him.

386
00:21:06,014 --> 00:21:09,108
All I wanna do is not think about the baby,
and I can't stop.

387
00:21:09,251 --> 00:21:15,019
Every time I move, I feel it here.
I feel this physical need to hold him.

388
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:18,956
How am I supposed to
not think about him?

389
00:21:19,094 --> 00:21:20,721
He's going to have a good life.

390
00:21:21,096 --> 00:21:24,862
You are going to have a good life.

391
00:21:25,534 --> 00:21:28,970
- I know, I know.
- Okay.

392
00:21:29,638 --> 00:21:31,697
Is it scary in there? In the NICU?

393
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:33,740
Is there someone talking to him?

394
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:35,809
It's not a scary place?

395
00:21:35,944 --> 00:21:39,505
I just have these terrible images of him
all alone,

396
00:21:39,648 --> 00:21:42,879
and I can't stand it.

397
00:21:43,018 --> 00:21:44,918
I can't.

398
00:21:48,357 --> 00:21:49,654
You wanna see him?

399
00:21:52,361 --> 00:21:54,352
Oh, God.

400
00:22:01,970 --> 00:22:05,201
Hey. I was saving that bottle
for an occasion.

401
00:22:05,674 --> 00:22:06,732
Oh.

402
00:22:06,875 --> 00:22:09,343
Yeah, occasion.

403
00:22:11,113 --> 00:22:13,911
- Are you having pain?
- It's okay.

404
00:22:17,786 --> 00:22:19,253
Mm.

405
00:22:20,555 --> 00:22:21,954
Except for drinking alone.

406
00:22:24,993 --> 00:22:28,156
Oh. I know you're uncomfortable.
You don't have to stay.

407
00:22:28,296 --> 00:22:31,094
I do. If I walk out the door,
all I'll do is think about you.

408
00:22:31,233 --> 00:22:33,599
Here, dying alone.

409
00:22:34,202 --> 00:22:36,227
I lived alone.

410
00:22:36,838 --> 00:22:37,930
You reap what you sow.

411
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:40,938
Sow carefully, my friend.

412
00:22:41,076 --> 00:22:46,207
[IN RUSSIAN ACCENT]
You don't want to end up tragic like me.

413
00:22:50,118 --> 00:22:55,556
It's small, contained, secure,

414
00:22:55,690 --> 00:22:59,956
but you're alone in there, Nora.

415
00:23:00,095 --> 00:23:04,623
I'm here with you,
but I'd be more here if you came out.

416
00:23:06,034 --> 00:23:07,899
NORA:
I can't.

417
00:23:10,372 --> 00:23:12,363
What are you afraid of?

418
00:23:14,976 --> 00:23:16,807
Everything.

419
00:23:17,546 --> 00:23:22,745
I feel it in the pit of my stomach.
It consumes me.

420
00:23:23,452 --> 00:23:26,785
People look at me, all those people.

421
00:23:26,922 --> 00:23:28,856
- And I feel scared.
- You're letting it get big.

422
00:23:28,990 --> 00:23:31,151
Let's break it down.

423
00:23:31,293 --> 00:23:33,659
I can't. Don't you see that?

424
00:23:33,795 --> 00:23:37,253
I'm letting my daughter down,
I'm letting everyone down,

425
00:23:37,399 --> 00:23:39,629
and I feel so scared.

426
00:23:39,768 --> 00:23:41,963
I mean, you've never felt this.
How can you know?

427
00:23:46,274 --> 00:23:47,502
I'm gonna break all the rules,

428
00:23:47,642 --> 00:23:50,440
and I'm gonna tell you something
about me.

429
00:23:52,881 --> 00:23:54,906
[SIGHS]

430
00:23:57,285 --> 00:24:02,086
I am more afraid
than I've ever been in my life.

431
00:24:02,891 --> 00:24:07,055
I'm pregnant.

432
00:24:07,729 --> 00:24:15,431
And that is paralyzingly,
terrifyingly scary for me.

433
00:24:17,372 --> 00:24:22,332
But I got up this morning
and I came to the office,

434
00:24:22,477 --> 00:24:23,774
because people needed me.

435
00:24:23,912 --> 00:24:26,244
And that's good, to be needed.

436
00:24:26,381 --> 00:24:28,315
To help you.

437
00:24:28,450 --> 00:24:33,046
And I'm using that to fight back my fear.

438
00:24:44,766 --> 00:24:47,530
NORA:
Motherhood is great.

439
00:24:48,103 --> 00:24:51,095
That's nothing to be afraid of.

440
00:24:52,541 --> 00:24:55,806
My daughter is the best part of my life.

441
00:25:00,315 --> 00:25:01,383
Then shouldn't you be at her wedding?

442
00:25:01,383 --> 00:25:02,975
Then shouldn't you be at her wedding?

443
00:25:06,421 --> 00:25:11,381
We all have fears,
me, you, your daughter.

444
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:15,324
Your daughter's scared her mother won't
be at her wedding, when she needs you.

445
00:25:15,463 --> 00:25:21,095
Maybe there's something scary
to be needed like that.

446
00:25:22,537 --> 00:25:25,301
Maybe that's why I'm scared.

447
00:25:27,175 --> 00:25:30,076
But we all have to face our fears.

448
00:25:31,112 --> 00:25:32,636
[SIGHS]

449
00:25:33,215 --> 00:25:37,618
And I think we both know that
my closet's not the answer.

450
00:25:56,605 --> 00:25:58,129
Well done.

451
00:26:00,609 --> 00:26:03,271
He's breathing much better now.

452
00:26:03,845 --> 00:26:05,005
[BABY COOING]

453
00:26:05,146 --> 00:26:07,614
Some things I can fix.

454
00:26:08,850 --> 00:26:10,374
Shh.

455
00:26:10,518 --> 00:26:11,849
I freaked out.

456
00:26:11,987 --> 00:26:14,683
- I couldn't think. I didn't know what to do.
- I called them.

457
00:26:14,823 --> 00:26:17,189
CARRIE: We made a mistake,
but we're here now.

458
00:26:17,859 --> 00:26:22,489
We wanna adopt him.
We've always wanted to adopt him.

459
00:26:22,697 --> 00:26:24,358
I'll talk to Judy.

460
00:26:24,499 --> 00:26:27,127
No. No.

461
00:26:27,269 --> 00:26:30,636
Judy, we screwed up.
We know what you must think.

462
00:26:30,772 --> 00:26:33,138
That you want him now,
when he's fixed?

463
00:26:33,275 --> 00:26:36,142
- It's not like that, Judy.
- You made me wanna give him to you.

464
00:26:36,278 --> 00:26:37,768
I thought you were the answer.

465
00:26:37,912 --> 00:26:40,642
And then when I needed you,
when he needed you...

466
00:26:48,690 --> 00:26:51,090
Uh, Judy.

467
00:26:56,131 --> 00:26:57,655
[GASPS]

468
00:26:58,199 --> 00:26:59,496
I'm keeping my baby.

469
00:27:02,771 --> 00:27:04,170
I'm keeping my son.

470
00:27:22,524 --> 00:27:24,549
Hi.

471
00:27:26,127 --> 00:27:28,357
VIOLET: Who can tell who's gonna be
a good parent and who won't?

472
00:27:28,496 --> 00:27:31,260
There's no litmus test and
it's really not our job to determine.

473
00:27:31,399 --> 00:27:33,890
She had the baby, it's her baby,
that's the way it works.

474
00:27:34,035 --> 00:27:38,165
It's an impulsive decision, and becoming
a parent should not be impulsive.

475
00:27:38,306 --> 00:27:41,070
But it is. Fate happens.

476
00:27:41,209 --> 00:27:45,578
No matter how much you think you
know what you want, things happen.

477
00:27:45,714 --> 00:27:49,377
And the best you can hope is that
people adjust to that change.

478
00:27:49,517 --> 00:27:53,078
I'm just worried because Judy was so clear
that she wanted to give up this baby.

479
00:27:53,221 --> 00:27:54,449
Actually, not so clear.

480
00:27:56,524 --> 00:27:58,924
After the Sinclairs got involved,
Judy's been on the fence.

481
00:27:59,060 --> 00:28:01,494
- And you withheld that?
- I didn't wanna make you nervous.

482
00:28:01,629 --> 00:28:04,393
Look, she stepped up when
no one else would. I mean,

483
00:28:04,532 --> 00:28:06,591
maybe it's for the best.

484
00:28:09,270 --> 00:28:10,794
[COOING]

485
00:28:11,306 --> 00:28:12,466
Hi.

